A ferry disaster off Java island left hundreds missing, with over 200 survivors found.
Survivors described the ship sinking quickly in rough seas, leaving little time for escape.
Rescue teams battled bad weather to locate survivors, dropping supplies to those stranded at sea.
Despite bloated bodies washing ashore, hope remained as more survivors were discovered.
Weeping relatives awaited news at hospitals, while search efforts continued.
The tragedy highlighted the dangers of Indonesia's vital ferry system, connecting thousands of islands.
The search for the missing persisted amid challenging conditions, with survivors' harrowing tales underscoring the urgency of rescue operations.
